data.chText: （教堂的）唱诗班；（公开演出的）合唱团，歌唱队

data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: a group of people who sing together, for example in church services or public performances
She sings in the school choir.
the part of a church where the choir sits during services

tr: the part of the chancel between sanctuary and nave
a chorus that sings as part of a religious ceremony
a family of similar musical instrument playing together

value.def: A choir is a group of people who sing together, for example in a church or school.

example.ex: He has been singing in his church choir since he was six.
example.tran: 他打6岁起一直在教堂唱诗班里唱歌。

value.tran: (教堂的)唱诗班;(学校的)合唱队，合唱团

value.def: In a church building, the choir is the area in front of the altar where the choir sits.

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to sing, to dance 歌, 舞
rootsaffixes.title: chor

partsOfSpeech.dec: chor 歌，舞 + al …的 → 唱诗班的
choreo〔= chor〕歌，舞 + graph 写，画 + er 表名词 → 写舞蹈的人 → 编舞者
choreo 歌，舞 + graph 写，画 + y 表行为 → 编舞
chor 歌，舞 + us 表名词，用于科学术语 → 合唱（队）
